title: Moses Celebrates After Assist For West Ham Vs Palace
text:
Headlines / Moses Celebrates After Assist For West Ham Vs Palace Moses Celebrates After Assist For West Ham Vs Palace Headlines 
By Adeboye Amosu: Victor Moses is delighted to see West Ham United beat his former side, Crystal Palace, at Selhurst Park on Saturday, Completesportsnigeria.com can report. The Nigerian winger, who has a close personal connection with Palace having started his professional career at the club, played a stirring role in West Ham United’s 3-1 win against the hosts. Moses set up Carl Jekinson for his side’s opening goal of the contest with a clever defence-splitting pass. He took to Twitter to praised his collegues for their performance in the game, while he also thanked the home fans for their support.“Great to be back at Selhurst Park yesterday and great win lads were brilliant! Thanks for the support,” he wrote on his Twitter handle on Sunday. The Super Eagles star is on loan at West Ham from Premier League champions, Chelsea.
